        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Once the first semester winds down, Johnston and McCrory will return to Duke swimming and diving. Johnston’s goal is to win another NCAA championship.
McCrory is on a break from training, but he said he resumes training in about a month. The junior has two more years of NCAA eligibility and says “he is looking forward to it.”</p>
<p>Are another Olympic Games in this duo’s future? It is not out of the realm of possibility, they both said.</p>
<p>“I want to go to medical school and that would put my life on hold for another year, so we’ll see,” Johnston said.</p>
<p>McCrory faces a similar choice.</p>
<p>“The next Olympics is four years way, which is a long time, but at the same time, the decision will make a difference in how I train now,” he said.</p>

